	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_rozenberg_ela">Eli Rozenberg</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/481)</p>

			<p>Original, manuscript, 2 pages, 235 x 340 mm, Polish language</p>

			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010481_01.jpg"/> I, <persName ref="#ehri_et_rozenberg_ela">Eli Rozenberg</persName>, born in <date
					when="1924">1924</date> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, at <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">25 Gęsia Street</placeName>. My father was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">murdered</term> by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> in <date when="1940">1940</date>. In
					<date when="1942-08">August 1942</date>, I was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject"
					>deported</term> from the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-1106" type="ghetto"
					>ghetto</placeName> to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName>
				along with the rest of my family, we were packed 100 to a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940"
					type="subject">wagon</term>. When the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject"
					>train</term> stopped, it was already dawn I saw the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765328/malkinia-gorna.html"
					>Małkinia</placeName> station through the little barred window, at that moment the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> started detaching groups of 15 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">wagons</term> that went on a special side-track
				leading to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">camp</term>, and when the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">wagons</term> stopped, they started shouting
						<q><foreign xml:lang="de">raus, raus</foreign></q>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
					type="subject">Women</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">separate</term>, saying good-bye to my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sisters</term>, I managed to get to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men’s</term> side, where the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> ordered us to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">sit on the ground</term>, telling us that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">baths</term> are here and that when we are bathed then
				everyone would be reunited with their family, would get new <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
					type="subject">clothing</term> and we would travel on further to where we would be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">working</term>. At this point a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> ran up to us as we were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">sitting</term> on the ground, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">picking out</term> 30 boys and me, telling us that we
				are going off to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>, happy that I would see
				my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sisters</term> again, we took us to a big <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-944" type="subject">yard</term> where there were huge piles of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothing</term>, suitcases, men’s and women’s shoes,
				baggage, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">money</term>, and mounds of other things,
				then the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> ordered us to take off our
				coats and start <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">working</term>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> consisted of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">sorting</term> every thing: shoes with shoes, coats
				with cots, etc. Not knowing anything about what was going on there, I asked a few boys, but no one gave me a real answer, I just found
				out that we were not permitted to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-658" type="subject">talk</term> to
				each other, suddenly I recognized someone I knew who used to live in one of the buildings in our courtyard, he was taken away 4 days
				before I was, so having asked him what this was here and where all the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were, he turned away, and with tears in
				his eyes, he told me just one word: <q>you don’t have any mother or sister any more</q>. Before he managed to tell me what happened to
				them and how, 2 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> ran up to us and
				started to thrash us in the head with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564" type="subject">whips</term>,
				then an additional 25 blows on our bare <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject"
					>bodies</term>. I got up from the ground with great difficulty, after we <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">sorted</term> things for another 2 hours until 10
				o'clock in the evening, they herded us to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
					>barracks</term>, suddenly they started shouting in German: they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-180" type="subject">stabbed</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_bialas_max">Maks</persName>
				<note type="gloss">SS‑Unterscharführer Max Bialas was killed on September 10 or 11, 1942 by Meir Berliner, a prisoner. As retaliation,
					the Germans killed 160 prisoners.</note> with a knife, who then was dying for a couple of hours, then they started to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">shoot</term> at us and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">torture</term> us mercilessly, with whatever they
				could. We pushed against each other like sheep, and when I fell to the ground, I was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">hit</term>on the fingers with a bayonet. After an hour
				of being chased like that, they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">killed</term> 100
				boys, including the hero [who had stabbed <persName ref="#ehri_et_bialas_max">Max</persName>], and chased us to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>, and it was only in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term> that I managed to rip a piece of my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">shirt</term> off to bandage my hand, each one of
				us laid down on the ground, crying and in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject"
					>pain</term>, to rest a little. The boys who had already been there for a few days or weeks already knew that we had to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">get up</term> when the light was still grayish outside
				and wait until they open the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>, but
				this time they didn’t open the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barracks</term>, they
				only <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-662" type="subject">threatened</term> us with machine guns and said
				that they would all kill us in a minute, so waiting impatiently for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829"
					type="subject">death</term>. They opened the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
					>barracks</term> only at 11 o'clock in the morning, shouting <q><foreign xml:lang="de">alles raus</foreign></q>, they put us in
				rows and took 200 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">boys</term> away, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">shot</term> them with a machine gun and herded the
				rest to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">punishing</term> them for 3 days by giving them no
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832">food</term> or water. In the afternoon, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> came to the group that was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">sorting</term> shoes and took 50 boys away including
				me, telling us that we were only going to do some light <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943"
					type="subject">work</term> for 10 minutes, and took us through the whole yard to some gate, and when we went through that gate my
				blood froze, I saw a heap of dead <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">people</term>
				lying on the ground, and bloodied boys going up to them with stretchers, grabbing <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> by the hands and legs, they laid them
				on the stretcher and ran away with them, thinking about all of this, I looked on with tears in my eyes, and all of a sudden I felt a
				blow to my head with a riding crop, the boys who were already there for a few days told us that two boys should take a stretcher and
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">carry</term>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515">corpses</term> to the pit, I went quickly to the
				stretcher, and taking the stretcher back, we went in the direction of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas chambers</term>, on the way <pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010481_02.jpg"/> to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gas
					chambers</term> they hit us with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-564" type="subject">whips</term>,
				shouting: <q>faster, you dogs</q>. I ran to the ramp quickly, we put the stretcher on the ground and clumsily laid the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpse</term> onto the stretcher, at this moment the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> began to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">torture</term> us mercilessly, they threw me to the
				ground and kicked me in the head, shouting that I hadn’t picked up the<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpse</term> the right way, that we were supposed to
				pick them up by the hands and feet and lay them down evenly on the stretcher. I got up off the ground with difficulty and taking the
				stretcher with my friend, we ran in the direction of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539"
					type="subject">pit</term>, on the way to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject"
					>pit</term> boys were running with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject"
					>corpses</term>, on after another, and coming closer to the<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539"
					type="subject">pit</term> I saw another tragic scene, in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539"
					type="subject">pit</term> I saw only a huge puddle of blood and when the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> were thrown into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">pit</term>, they sunk into the blood, I carried <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> for a whole month, then they moved me
				to the ramp, that <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-558" type="subject">work</term> was very hard, pulling
				out <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gassed</term>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515">corpses</term>. I pulled out <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> for 5 months, all of those <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> were thrown into <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">pits</term> and spread with chlorine, in <date
					when="1943-02">1943, in February</date>, the order was issued to dig out all those <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515">corpses</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-516" type="subject">burn</term> them, so 3 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">diggers</term> were brought in that lowered their
				buckets into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">pit</term> and grabbed the pieces
				of flesh and bones with their teeth and then threw them onto the ground above, boys standing nearby with pitchforks put the pieces of
				flesh and bones on stretchers and took them to the fire, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-516"
					type="subject">burning</term> 8 thousand people a day.</p>
